			<div class="content" id="post-content-3820745">
									

<p>Rimworld. I fucking <em>love</em> rimworld.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;show&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>Its just such an expansive game, it, it can generate awesome stories, its incredible addictive, fuck I once played for six hours straight. Seriously, on the steam thingy, the overlay, 360 minutes. And theres just so much to do! <em>Especially</em> with mods, I could talk about all the different mods there are forever. It's got such a great modding community, there are mods that completely overhaul the game, there are mods that add spaceships, or nuclear reactors, or, or advanced psychology, or a whole bunch of medieval shit, or a whole bunch of glittertech shit, its insane, and its all on the steam workshop too, so you can just sit down for thirty minutes and amass an insane amount of mods with ease, its awesome. And I love how it can just make you do crazy shit, it brings out my inner psychopath better than dwarf fuckin fortress, like there have literally been points where i'm watching people burning to death and laughing like a james bond villain. I must've looked crazy. I literally once took somebody, harvested <em>all</em> of the organs possible while still keeping them alive<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-376982-1" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-376982-1')">1</a></sup> and then built a specially designed execution chamber specifically so I could burn them to death. I went ahead and burned 'em within an inch of their life, and then put out the fire and left them to die of starvation - while covered in horrific, agonizing burn wounds! Ahhh, memories&#8230; and there are so many other stories, too.</p>
<p>There was that time 30% of the population of my colony died from drug overdose in a single day, there was that time when I sent one guy to ride around a herd of insane turtles on deerback to shoot them with a crossbow, there was that time when two consecutive raids breached my walls and all my colonists had to pick up guns and fight.</p>
<p>And the colonists too, their really interesting. I remember I had one - Bowman, if i remember correctly - that was just like the best colonist. Decked out with a high quality charge rifle and a shit ton of advanced bionics, she could move at insane speeds and had ridiculous accuracy. She was killed in a mechaniod raid, and I was going to revive her, but the body was mushed to bits when I sent in one of my droids as a suicide bomber. I had to revive her partner in crime Markus instead.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p><em>heavy breathing</em></p>
<p>So yeah. Oh, and hello gears. Haven't seen you in&#8230; ever, actually. You last were on the site before I joined, I'm pretty sure. Read anything nice lately? Caught up on dado and the dickbottle?</p>
