<p>I have a friend who is bloody mental for rimworld, and I keep meaning to get it myself. I love building bases, and the dizzying amount of freedom and lunacy it provides is very appealing. An amusing story: My friend had recently gotten some eldrich mod, that allows elder evils, horrors, and cultists to come in to play. Of course, this sounded amazing, so like everyone we cobbled together a stranded group based on various relations and friends, ourselves included. The game proceeded to start, and low and behold, a black, foreboding obelisk was found in short order, sheltered in some rubble.</p>
<p>It took my in-game avatar precisely one day to then creep out in the dead of night, go briefly mad, then pen the Necronomicon. I'm laughing and trying to plead &quot;I mean, someone was going to, it's there!&quot; to which he replied &quot;Of fucking course it'd be you!&quot; Very fun.</p>

