<p>Oh shit gears is alive <sup>muffled fangirl noises</sup>.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;so&nbsp;vidyagaimz&nbsp;huh</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;I&nbsp;know&nbsp;a&nbsp;thing&nbsp;or&nbsp;two&nbsp;about&nbsp;those</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>But for the point of the post: Someone else already mentioned Dwarf Fortress, only on passing tho. So it's my sacred duty to tell you more about it.</p>
<p>So dwarf fortress&#8230; Basically if you find rimworld too simple and approachable try DF. The UI will give you nightmares the control scheme is horrible, and the graphics&#8230; who am I kidding it doesn't have graphics. But the things you can do, the stories you create. Once you get past the point you fortress dies of starvation or thirst (or because you spawned in top of a tree that your lumberjack cut, and all your dwarfs die to their untimely deaths. It has happened to me), you can get to the truly good suff: Start a functional agricultural society, produce manufacturated goods, forge weapons and armor, arm an army with said weapons, train said army, <span style="text-decoration: line-through;">have them die horribly to the first wave of invaders</span> beat the combined siege of all the forces of evil in the region, engage in trade, meddle in dwarf politics, <span style="text-decoration: line-through;">create your own cult of vampires</span>, create artifacts, build your very own coliseum or an actual functional calculator, you now normal stuff.</p>
<p>And if that's not up your alley you can always try adventurer mode and try your hand at becoming a hero in those randomly generated lands (did I mention every workd is randomly generated, each one with their own method and mythology). Once you get past the overwhelming character creation, you can go into the overwhelming world where you are free to do whatever you please. It's specially fun when after going around killing some animals and kobolds, you find an actual opponent with weapons and combat skill, and the he wipes the floor with your mangled corpse just before eating it raw (did I mention you can quench your thirst by drinking the blood of your enemies? No not like a vampire, the process to become a vampire or a werebeast is different).</p>
<p>Considering this is getting quite long. The best thing about it. ITS COMPLETELY FREE. So yeah if you end up checking it out consult the dfwiki makes your life so much easier.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>So yeah&#8230; Anyway it's good to see you are back.</p>

