			<div class="content" id="post-content-3820827">
									

<p>My game of choice is Guild Wars 2. I’m not much of an MMO person in general, but an old buddy got me into GW2 six years ago and here I’ve stayed. I’m irretrievably wrapped up in the story and lore <span style="text-decoration: line-through;">(I killed a god and I liked iiit&#8230;)</span>, and there’s gameplay for all skill levels, and people help each other, and it’s just great.</p>
<p>I’ve also recently started playing my beloved Sims 2 again. Some people play as malevolent deities, erasing pool ladders and toilets&#8230;I play it to make Sims of my friends and report back on their shenanigans. (I may or may not have plans to blog the adventures of a household of old-school SCP author avatars. That means you, Gears.)</p>
<p>Other games I play include Minesweeper, Fallen London (I’m firmly pushing my way forth into a self-destructive quest to&#8230;achieve some unclear end involving seven candles and a betrayed eldritch abomination), various Zelda titles, and a bit of chess.</p>
<p>&#8230;and of course, I pine eternally for the days when I could have added #scpmafia to that list.</p>

